We need to unify how buildgit shows a build in progress.  There are 2 ways this tool can show a build in progress.  One is through 'buildgit status -f'.  
The other is 'buildgit push'

I want to change this so that the output of these commands looks roughly the same and it gives us the infomration we need when a build is in progress.

not enough info:

```bash
$ echo "#" >> nonsensebuildtrigger.md && ./jbuildmon/buildgit add nonsensebuildtrigger.md && ./jbuildmon/buildgit commit -m 'test123' && ./jbuildmon/buildgit push
[main b372452] test123
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
To ssh://scranton2:2233/home/git/ralph1.git
   1905bd5..b372452  main -> main
[14:19:34] ℹ Verifying Jenkins connectivity...
[14:19:34] ✓ Connected to Jenkins
[14:19:34] ℹ Verifying job 'ralph1' exists...
[14:19:34] ✓ Job 'ralph1' found
[14:20:00] ℹ   Stage: Initialize Submodules (10s)
```

buildgit status -f output:

```bash

$ ./jbuildmon/buildgit status -f
On branch main
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

